<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 4:31PM EDT  by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg</headline>
<description>...A HEAVY RAIN SHOWER WILL IMPACT SOUTHWESTERN CATAWBA...
NORTHWESTERN LINCOLN...NORTH CENTRAL CLEVELAND AND SOUTHEASTERN BURKE
COUNTIES UNTIL 515 PM EDT...
At 430 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a heavy rain shower 15
miles southeast of Morganton, or 5 miles northeast of Casar, moving
east at 10 mph.
Locations to be impacted include...
Casar, Belwood, Cooksville, Propst, Pleasant Grove and Vale.
Very heavy rainfall rates up to 2 inches per hour will be possible in
these areas.</description>
